name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Capital Mall - 625 Black Lake Boulevard Southwest, Olympia WA, 98502
info: This is a Johnson & Johnson clinic being held at Capital Mall, 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502 for anyone age 18 and older from 12pm-8pm.  We will be located inside the mall, closest to the Sephora end of the mall and next to the Buckle store. Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers, if needed. • Please arrive at your scheduled appointment time. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Bucoda Community Center - 101A E 7th St, Bucoda WA, 98530
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. 

This is a walk in clinic being held at Bucoda Community Center - 101A E 7th St., Bucoda WA, 98530 from 4 - 7pm. • All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
address: 1235 North Post St. Suite 201, Spokane WA, 99205
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer or Moderna COVID-19 vaccine or the single dose of the Johnson & Johnson*** All patients 12 years old and older can register for the Pfizer vaccine only. (If 12-17 years old for the Pfizer vaccine, you must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. 
***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
